#: ../../C/CP-M.rst:9
msgid ""
"[Control Program/Monitor; later :ref:`retcon`\\ned to Control Program for "
"Microcomputers] An early microcomputer :ref:`OS` written by hacker Gary "
"Kildall for 8080- and Z80-based machines, very popular in the late 1970s but"
" virtually wiped out by MS-DOS after the release of the IBM PC in 1981. "
"Legend has it that Kildall's company blew its chance to write the OS for the"
" IBM PC because Kildall decided to spend a day IBM's reps wanted to meet "
"with him enjoying the perfect flying weather in his private plane (another "
"variant has it that Gary's wife was much more interested in packing her "
"suitcases for an upcoming vacation than in clinching a deal with IBM). Many "
"of CP/M's features and conventions strongly resemble those of early "
":ref:`DEC` operating systems such as :ref:`TOPS-10`\\, OS/8, RSTS, and "
"RSX-11. See :ref:`MS-DOS`\\, :ref:`operating-system`\\."
msgstr ""
"[Control Program/Monitor。後にControl Program for Microcomputersに\\ "
":ref:`retcon`\\ された] ハッカーGary "
"Kildallが8080およびZ80ベースのマシン向けに書いた初期のマイクロコンピューター\\ :ref:`OS`\\ "
"で、1970年代後半に非常に人気がありましたが、1981年のIBM PCの発売後にMS-"
"DOSによって事実上一掃されました。伝説によれば、Kildallの会社がIBM "
"PC向けのOSを書く機会を逃したのは、IBMの担当者が会いたがっていた日に、Kildallが自家用機で絶好の飛行日和を楽しむことに費やすと決めたためだとされています(別の説では、Garyの妻がIBMとの取引をまとめるよりも、来るべき休暇のためにスーツケースに荷物を詰めることにはるかに興味を持っていたとされています)。CP/Mの機能や慣習の多くは、\\"
" :ref:`TOPS-10`\\ 、OS/8、RSTS、RSX-11といった初期の\\ :ref:`DEC`\\ "
"オペレーティングシステムのものに強く似ています。\\ :ref:`MS-DOS`\\ 、\\ :ref:`operating-system`\\ "
"を参照。"
